A crisis is looming in the education sector following widespread reports that english language and kiswahili language text books which were recently provided to form one students all over the country have gross grammatical and factual errors. Several schools have pointed out the errors which if left unattended might destabilize learning in secondary schools further stating that the rush to beat the January 12th deadline set by the government to deliver textbooks might be to blame. The Chairman of the Kenyan Publishers Association, Lawrence Njagi despite acknowledged a mistake says that it did not warrant a mass panic. 